@node Overview
@chapter Overview

@samp{org-noter-extras.el} extends @samp{org-noter}, the package that facilitates taking interleaved notes on PDF documents within Org mode. When @samp{org-noter} creates skeleton annotations from PDF highlights, the resulting headings are generic (``Highlight on page N'') and the extracted text often contains hyphenation artifacts from the PDF layout engine. @samp{org-noter-extras.el} provides a suite of commands to clean up, reformat, and navigate these annotations more efficiently.

The package provides the following capabilities:

@itemize
@item
@strong{Annotation cleanup.} A command to replace generic highlight headings with custom titles and wrap the extracted text in quote blocks (@ref{Annotation cleanup}).
@item
@strong{Annotation merging.} A command to merge the contents of two adjacent annotations into one, useful when a single passage spans multiple highlights (@ref{Merging annotations}).
@item
@strong{Dehyphenation.} Functions to remove hyphenation artifacts from text extracted from PDFs, where words broken across lines retain their hyphens (@ref{Dehyphenation}).
@item
@strong{Page offset correction.} A command to adjust page numbers in annotation headings when the PDF page numbers differ from the printed page numbers (@ref{Page offset correction}).
@item
@strong{Navigation.} Commands to move between notes while keeping focus in the Org buffer rather than switching to the PDF viewer (@ref{Navigation}).
@end itemize

The package depends on @samp{org-noter}.

