@node Dehyphenation characters
@section Dehyphenation characters

@vindex org-noter-extras-dehyphenate-hyphens
The constant @code{org-noter-extras-dehyphenate-hyphens} holds a list of strings representing hyphen characters that should be treated as word-break markers by the dehyphenation functions. Its default value is @samp{("-" "¬")}, covering the standard ASCII hyphen and the not sign (@samp{U+00AC}), which some PDF extraction tools produce in place of soft hyphens. You can change the active hyphen character interactively with @code{org-noter-extras-set-hyphen} (@ref{Dehyphenation}).

@node Heading and quote patterns
@section Heading and quote patterns

@vindex org-noter-highlight-heading-regexp
@vindex org-noter-quote-begin
@vindex org-noter-quote-end
Several constants define the patterns that @samp{org-noter-extras.el} uses to identify and manipulate annotation structures:

The constant @code{org-noter-highlight-heading-regexp} matches the default heading format that @samp{org-noter} creates for highlight annotations: @samp{"Highlight on page[s]? \\(.*\\)"}. The first capture group extracts the page number or page range. This pattern is used by the cleanup, merge, and offset commands.

The constant @code{org-noter-quote-begin} holds the string @samp{"\n#+begin_quote\n"}, used when wrapping annotation content in an Org quote block during cleanup (@ref{Annotation cleanup}).

The constant @code{org-noter-quote-end} holds the string @samp{"\n#+end_quote\n"}, matching the end of the quote block.

