@node Extracting annotation contents
@section Extracting annotation contents

@findex org-noter-get-annotation-contents
The function @code{org-noter-get-annotation-contents} extracts and cleans the text from an @samp{org-noter} annotation subtree. It determines whether point is on a ``Highlight on page'' heading or a ``Contents'' heading, narrows to the content region, fills the text with a very large @code{fill-column} (effectively unwrapping all lines), runs @code{org-noter-extras-dehyphenate} to remove hyphenation artifacts (@ref{Dehyphenation}), and returns the cleaned text as a string.

This function is used internally by @code{org-noter-extras-cleanup-annotation} (@ref{Annotation cleanup}) and @code{org-noter-extras-merge-contents-with-next} (@ref{Merging annotations}).

